[30;1m16 | [0m[35m    default = 'Sort format: {FIELD:ORDER}'[0m

[30;1m20 | [0m[35m    The plugins iterator provides a scalable way to work through plugin result[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    sets of any size.  The iterator will walk through each page of data,[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    returning one record at a time.  If it reaches the end of a page of[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    records, then it will request the next page of information and then continue[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    to return records from the next page (and the next, and the next) until the[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    counter reaches the total number of records that the API has reported.[0m

[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    result sets of any size.  The iterator will walk through each page of data,[0m

[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    then it will request the next page of information and then continue to[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    return records from the next page (and the next, and the next) until the[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    counter reaches the total number of records that the API has reported.[0m

[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    The ad object iterator provides a scalable way to work through alert list[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    result sets of any size. The iterator will walk through each page of data,[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    returning one record at a time. If it reaches the end of a page of[0m

[30;1m62 | [0m[35mNote the tilda, informing the filtering engine that it will need to perform some[0m
[30;1m63 | [0m[35msort of calculation first.  The tilda is only used when using the asset filter.[0m
[30;1m64 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35mNow for a more complex calculation, you could look for the IPs that exist in[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35mboth 1 or 2, but not 3:[0m

[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    The API iterator provides a scalable way to work through result sets of any[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    size.  The iterator will walk through each page of data, returning one[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    record at a time.  If it reaches the end of a page of records, then it will[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    request the next page of information and then continue to return records[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m    from the next page (and the next, and the next) until the counter reaches[0m
[30;1m27 | [0m[35m    the total number of records that the API has reported.[0m

[30;1m3 | [0m[35m============[0m
